            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> I think this is a great idea, and really like the aesthetics of `nvim-pqf`. My only concern is the alignment of text of the quickfix content on long filepaths (although I think the alignment looks more aesthetic personally)\r\n\r\nIn an early implementation of this in my dotfiles, I trimmed the file paths to three segments. I got rid of that in [this commit](https://gitlab.com/yorickpeterse/dotfiles/-/commit/c8252f22afafa6e2288ace3b7c3a1b9800255426) because I ended up not liking it as much as I'd hoped.\r\n\r\nLong file paths haven't been an issue for myself, though I imagine it gets annoying for some (e.g. Java projects with their whole `src/main/org/foo/bar/bla/factory/whatever` file paths). I'm not sure what a good way of dealing with this is.",
