            "body": "> I thought about using `conceal`, and wrapping special elements in certain start/end tokens (e.g. `<loc>line:column</loc>`), but that's going to mess things up when you try to yank text from an item. I also think this will introduce issues if the item text includes those tags.\n\nThere's a great and easy and IMO fancy workaround for this and is using the `TextYankPost` event to search and replace the conceal tags/tokens. I've personally implemented this in a plugin and is pretty easy an performant with Lua. \n\nAs the command also provides the register you just replace the register contents.\n\nAbout the items having the tags, it's just an issue of using unique enough token/tags in te text to do the conceal. ",
